The respondent in case DIS-IHK-2025-01180 asserts that the Deutsche Institution für Schiedsgerichtsbarkeit e.V.(DIS) lacks jurisdiction to administer the dispute. The respondent bases this assertion on clause 6.2 of the Engagement Letter dated July 1, 2020. According to the respondent, clause 6.2 stipulates that all disputes arising from the agreement shall be settled under the Rules of the Munich Chamber of Commerce Rules of Arbitration by a single arbitrator. The respondent argues that there is no agreement to submit disputes to DIS, therefore DIS lacks jurisdiction.

Elcomponics Sales Pvt. Ltd. ("Respondent") submitted a response to the Request for Arbitration dated 6th May 2025 filed by FAMAS Gmbh. The Respondent raised a jurisdictional objection to the arbitration request. This response was submitted on behalf of Elcomponics Sales Pvt. Ltd. by its duly authorized Company Secretary, Anu Sharma, who is authorized to represent the company in this matter. The Respondent contends that the Request for Arbitration is inadmissible and requests that DIS decline jurisdiction over the matter.

The document references a "request for arbitration" between Famas GmbH and Elcomponics Sales. It mentions the absence of consent to DIS arbitration, stating that the respondent has never been asked to consent nor has consented to arbitration under DIS rules. The document also refers to arbitration rules (IHK Munchen) and notes that there is no provision in the Engagement Letter permitting submission of disputes to DIS or adoption of DIS procedural rules. This suggests a dispute regarding the applicable arbitration rules and forum.

The Respondent contends that the Request for Arbitration is inadmissible because DIS (presumably an arbitration institution) lacks jurisdiction to administer the dispute. The Respondent argues that submitting the dispute to DIS is inconsistent with the parties' agreement and represents an attempt by the Claimant to unilaterally impose a forum not agreed upon in the Engagement Letter. Consequently, the Respondent requests that DIS decline jurisdiction over the matter. The Respondent reserves the right to submit further evidence, arguments, or documentation to support this jurisdictional objection and to engage legal counsel if necessary.

FaMAS gmbh issued an invoice to Elcomponics Sales Pvt Ltd for a transaction fee related to an engagement letter signed on July 1, 2020. The invoice details a transaction value estimated at EUR 7 million for 26% of the shares of Invictus, with a total fee of EUR 245,000. The payment terms specified are immediate upon receipt, and the amount is net of bank charges, which must be covered by the client. Additionally, the invoice notes that VAT is subject to the importation rules of the client's country. This transaction reflects a significant financial engagement between the two companies, indicating a potential investment or acquisition.
